Node.Notes: Apparently refers to incident recorded in 1s21:10-22:1. Unknown why Abimelech rather than Achish is mentioned. One potential explanation: Abimelech ("my father is king") is a title for Philistine kings and so refers to Achish after all.
Uncertain whether refers to psalmist himself or a generic reference to all who are helpless/poor.
Expresses the protection given to those who fear Yahweh.
(SYNTAX) Assumes "who" from first part. Alternative would be to do NpNp with "the man," thus forming one clause.
Implied subject may be the righteous from v. 16 or the broken hearted in v. 19 (delayed subject).
